OL,3,CMan posing as a taxi driver jailed for
OL,4,Craping woman decade after similar case
OL,6,FHaving pleaded not guilty and instead
OL,7,Ftrying to blame the victim for his
OL,8,Fshocking crime, prosecutors with CPS
OL,9,FWessex dismantled Tariq's lies by
OL,10,Fcompiling strong forensic, witness and
OL,11,Fphone evidence at trial to secure a
OL,12,Fconviction for rape.
OL,14,FCrucially, the prosecution also
OL,15,Fsucceeded in putting forward bad
OL,16,Fcharacter evidence which outlined to
OL,17,Fthe jury how Tariq had committed a
OL,18,Fnear-identical crime in 2011. They
OL,19,Fmade the case that his previous
OL,20,Fconviction was relevant to the trial
OL,21,Fand could be disclosed.
